race.comment: CHARLBURY (11) missed the money two runs ago and again finished just outside the frame last start over 2100m at Tauranga, ending up fifth without having much luck. She slides down in class here and is ready to put her best hoof forward. Each way value. LACHIE (8) has been improving this prep, finishing well back at Te Aroha first-up before scoring by nearly a length over 1600m there last time out 11 days ago. He will relish the extra 500m and could go back-to-back. KIWI SKYHAWK (4) was close up last start when fifth over 1600m here after settling well back, and then running on strongly over the concluding stages. He should appreciate the extra distance and is a genuine each-way chance. BALANCE OF POWER (2) produced a solid third over 2200m at Te Aroha last time out, and he will be peaking at the right time here. With a cosy run early on from his inside draw, he will be right in the finish again.
